1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of LDPC codes, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper proposes an approach to estimate the performance of quantized LDPC decoders, which involves evaluating lower bounds on the frame error rate. This could be seen as a computational complexity problem. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - LDPC codes are widely used in communication systems, and the paper discusses the performance of LDPC decoders in the context of message passing algorithms. This could be relevant to the networking and internet architecture community. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper uses different classes of LDPC codes to demonstrate the robustness of the proposed approach. This could be relevant to the social and information networks community, which often deals with network analysis and optimization. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes an approach to estimate the performance of LDPC decoders based on lower bounds on the frame error rate. This could be seen as a problem in data structures and algorithms.
